    "notes": [
      {
        "category": "summary",
        "text": "An update is available for ca-certificates.\nThis update affects Rocky Linux 8 from CIQ.\nA Common Vulnerability Scoring System (CVSS) base score, which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVE list",
        "title": "Topic"
      },
      {
        "category": "description",
        "text": "The ca-certificates package contains a set of Certificate Authority (CA) certificates chosen by the Mozilla Foundation for use with the Internet Public Key Infrastructure (PKI).\n\nBug Fix(es) and Enhancement(s):\n\n* Annual 2024 ca-certificates update version 2.69 from NSS 3.101.1 for Firefox 128 [Rocky Linux from CIQ-8.10] (JIRA:Rocky Linux-44949)\n\n* ca-certificates: python-certifi: Removal of e-Tugra root certificate [Rocky Linux from CIQ-8.10.0.z] (JIRA:Rocky Linux-16194)\n\nThis advisory is provided by CIQ Inc for Rocky Linux systems. For more information about CIQ security practices, visit https://ciq.com/security.",
        "title": "Description"
      }
    ],
    "aggregate_severity": {
      "text": "Critical"
